<h2>Instrument Calibration</h2>

<p>The department has a long history of calibration of complete
space-borne instruments, in addition to the design, manufacture and
testing of satellite instrument sub-systems. The list to date is shown
below.</p>

<p>Most recently, the HIRDLS calibration was successfully completed at the end of
2002 in the custom-built <a
href="../facilities/2point2_metre_facility/index.html">2.2 metre
calibration facility</a>. The calibration of ATSR-2 was completed in
1993 in the <a href="../facilities/1point6_metre_chamber.html">1.6 metre facility</a>.</p>
<ul>
<li>The High Resolution Dynamics Limb Sounder (<a
href="../../hirdls/home.htm">HIRDLS</a>) on <a href="http://aura.gsfc.nasa.gov/">EOS Aura</a>
<li>The Along Track Scanning Radiometer (<a
href="http://www.atsr.rl.ac.uk/">ATSR-2</a>) on <a href="http://earth.esa.int/ers/">ERS-2</a>
<li>The Along Track Scanning Radiometer (<a href="http://www.atsr.rl.ac.uk/">ATSR-1</a>) on <a href="http://earth.esa.int/ers/">ERS-1</a>
<li>The Improved Statospheric and Mesospheric Sounder (<a
href="../../group/isams">ISAMS</a>) on <a href="http://umpgal.gsfc.nasa.gov/">UARS</a>
<li>The Statospheric and Mesospheric Sounder (<a
href="http://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/database/MasterCatalog?sc=1978-098A&ex=2">SAMS</a>) flown
on <a href="http://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/earth/nimbus.html">Nimbus 7</a>
<li>The Pressure Modulator Radiometer (<a href="http://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/database/MasterCatalog?sc=1975-052A&ex=9">PMR</a>) on <a href="http://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/earth/nimbus.html">Nimbus 6</a>
<li>The Selective Chopper Radiometer (<a
href="http://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/database/MasterCatalog?sc=1972-097A&ex=2">SCR</a>) on <a href="http://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/earth/nimbus.html">Nimbus 5</a>
</ul>
<BR>
